      • getAvailability

        @Nullable
ProductVariantAvailability getAvailability()
        The availability is set if the variant is tracked by the inventory. The field might not contain the latest inventory state (it is eventually consistent) and can be used as an optimization to reduce calls to the inventory service.
        Returns:
        availability

      • isMatchingVariant

        @Nullable
Boolean isMatchingVariant()
        A flag that indicates whether the variant matches the search criteria used when requesting the list of products or not. This flag is needed since all products that have at least one matching variant will be returned, along with all its variants, even those that do not match the search request themselves. Notice that this flag is only set when using the ProductProjection Search endpoint.
        Returns:
        whether the variant matches the search request parameters

      • getIdentifier

        @Nullable
ByIdVariantIdentifier getIdentifier()
        Gets the id of the product and the variant. This operation may not be available. It will be available if this ProductVariant has been created by loading a Product or a ProductProjection from JSON.
        Returns:
        identifier for this variant
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if the operation is not available
